caption: I took a chance with this place on DoorDash. I picked up the food and the woman was very unpleasant when getting my food. As far as the food, I wanted a lunch and thought you couldn’t go airbag with chicken wings and fried rice?! Typical urban Chinese trash food. Sorry but don’t waste your money!

I have been getting food from here for the 6.5 years I have lived in DC and it has always been delicious! The portions are generous, the sushi lunch special is a great deal, and the staff has always been consistently so wonderful and kind (one time I was running late getting home and the delivery man beat me to my apartment, but then he bicycled over to where I was!). I am glad to see that they are still open, and that even from the start of COVID their policies have been great to keep everyone safe. I will seriously consider if I am still in the delivery radius the next time that I have to move

The staff was slow and unconcerned, some places are open late and this place is one, as a delivery driver, when you get to a restaurant that claims the food is ready at a certain time, this place is well liked, however everyone benefits from punctuality, and even though the customer was happy, maybe hire a chef?

I have always sworn by this restaurant. Everything is always delicious. But today must have really been an off day. I didn’t even recognize the chicken wings which are normally large and juicy. Today’s were the smallest wings I have ever seen, as well as dried out. The wonton soup was excellent, but the chicken teriyaki was unrecognizable as such. There were two skewers of vegetables, sliced chicken, and a small container of sauce. I didn’t know what to make of it. I hope this restaurant goes back to its deliciousness.

Loved this place. The crispy beef was so-so, but everything else was A+ delicious. We even ended up using the leftover sauce from the Szechuan Chili beef to season a brisket we put in a Crock-Pot the day after. Highly recommend.
Best Asian food I've had in a while!

I have been ordering from One Fish Two Fish for about five years, and it is consistently delicious. The staff is consistently so kind, and the delivery drives are consistently fast and wonderful. Delicious vegetarian options. One of the best lunch deals around. Phenomenal and delicious food for a very good price!  The inside is also beautiful and has the sky painted on the ceiling as a really fun touch!  And, in these trying COVID-19 times, their delivery drivers have one of the best no touch delivery methods. Please consider supporting them since I cannot imagine how much business they’ve lost since GW closed, as that was where I first heard of them.  I strongly recommend the TVP sesame chicken or the pork pho! But my go to order will always be their crab rangoon and kung pao tofu!
Decent food and okay service! Crispy spring rolls were great!

Regular customer, after a recent delivery, the quality of their food is going down, onions in the thai curry were raw and even after telling them on phone to add no spice to the curry, it was extremely spicy and gave a stomach ache afterwards.

Their food is very good. However, last night, I ordered the Crispy Lemon Chicken which was quite good but the problem was that the chicken was not crispy (fried), it was grilled. Actually, nothing in the dish was crispy so I don't know if they mistakenly put grilled chicken in the dish or if that is what they consider crispy. Misleading name and I will be bringing it to their attention

Despite its location in a very unassuming basement, this is a very solid spot for takeout Chinese.  You occasionally see people eating inside; however, most people are just waiting to pick up their orders and take home.  As long as you are expecting take out Chinese and not fine dining, you won't be disappointed.  The employees are all very kind and, if you are looking to veer away from your standard order, open to offering some suggestions.  There are reviews saying that their dishes lack spice/flavor.  They are more than happy to add on should you request.  I decided tonight was a 1 Fish 2 Fish night.  It was miserably rainy and cold so I thought it would be easier to dine in for the first time as opposed to carry out and having my paper bag of food soaked.  I also branched out and got their 6 piece sashimi special and MAN did my life change.  For $10 you get 6 pieces of very generously thick sashimi.  Their default is 2 salmon, 2 tuna, and 2 white tuna that's accompanied by a carrot and cucumber salad as well as a bowl of miso.  It was delicious and the staff were all just as kind as they are at take out.  I will definitely be returning for more sashimi, dine in, and order changes!

Vegetarians BEWARE!  I was so excited to find this restaurant near me.  They had an entire TVP section, which is so refreshing to have some better vegetarian options.  The TVP Sesame Chicken I ordered today was 100% was chicken.  I ordered on Eat24 so there was no mistake over a misunderstood phone order.  I've had their TVP before, so I am certain without any doubt that what i was given was chicken.  I called to discuss it with the restaurant, and the guy who answered the phone could not have cared less...their only suggestion was that I call Eat24.  I haven't eaten meat in fifteen years, and the incredibly non apologetic response from 1 Fish 2 Fish is so disappointing.  I highly suggest not purchasing food from this restaurant.

This is a take-out chinese restaurant with dine-in option.  Like a previous reviewer, I experienced the waitress becoming easily annoyed with a couple questions outside of taking your order. I've gotten take out there before, and will probably do so again when I can't think of any other place, but I vow never to dine-in again due to the terrible wait service.
